description.content:
Gets an object which has the location of the documents containing the restrictions of an authority.
The documentation provided here shows the model you will find at these locations. The initial object contains only the URL's. You will have to fetch the documents from these URL's

query.description: (Required) The ID of the authority. You can find this by making a request to the getAll endpoint
Format - date-time (as date-time in RFC3339). The date at which you wish to view the restrictions

description.content:
Gets an object which has the location of the documents containing the public restrictions of an authority.
The documentation provided here shows the model you will find at these locations. The initial object contains only the URL's. You will have to fetch the documents from these URL's.
This endpoint returns only public information. To fetch the full information, use the getFullBySlug or getFullById endpoints

query.description: (Required) The name of the authority. You can find this by making a request to the getAll endpoint
Format - date-time (as date-time in RFC3339). The date at which you wish to view the restrictions
